com.pholser.junit.quickcheck.generator

Interface GenerationStatus


  • public interface GenerationStatus
    Generators are fed instances of this interface on each generation so that, if they choose, they can use these instances to influence the results of a generation for a particular property parameter.

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Interface and Description
      static class  GenerationStatus.Key<T>
      Type-safe keys for setValue and valueOf.

    • Method Summary

    • Method Detail

      • size

        int size()
        Returns:
        an arbitrary "size" parameter; this value (probabilistically) increases for every successful generation

      • attempts

        int attempts()
        Returns:
        how many attempts have been made to generate a value for a property parameter

      • setValue

        <T> GenerationStatus setValue(GenerationStatus.Key<T> key,
                              T value)
        Associates the given value with the given key for the duration of the generation of a value for a property parameter, or until overwritten.
        Type Parameters:
        T - type of the value
        Parameters:
        key - a key to associate with a value
        value - the associated value
        Returns:
        self, so that calls to this method can be chained

      • valueOf

        <T> Optional<T> valueOf(GenerationStatus.Key<T> key)
        Retrieves the value associated with the given key.
        Type Parameters:
        T - type of the value associated with the key
        Parameters:
        key - key to look up
        Returns:
        the (optional) associated value
